description:
**Kevuru Games** is a leading European art production and game development studio engaged in creating transformative entertainment projects for clients from all over the world.


* **Top 10 world game publishers.** We successfully deliver projects for such giants of the gaming industry as Lucasfilm, Epic Games and EA.
* **Long-term client partnership.** Our average client partnership extends to 3+ years thanks to a deep understanding of the needs of the client and the high quality of work.
* **Top 20 world best PC games.** Our team contributed to games like Fortnite, Star Wars: Tales from the Galaxy’s Edge and more – you can always take a closer look at our projects.
* **100+** **million active gamers.** Players around the world enjoy the games developed in partnership with Kevuru Games.


**Main corporate facts about us:**


* **166%** employee growth in 2021.
* **350+** talented artists and highly skilled game developers.
* **60%** senior specialists, both carefully hunted and lovingly grown from juniors in the company.
* **11** years of experience in the global gaming industry.


All our employees choose what they are interested in doing, and we, in turn, provide them with a smooth, understandable and transparent way of professional development, as well as guarantee them the most comfortable working conditions and perks.



We are looking for a **Level Designer.**


#### **REQUIREMENTS****:**


* Experience as a Level Designer in the gaming industry 1 year+;
* Strong understanding of game mechanics, and level flow;
* Proficiency in balancing difficulty curves and ensuring a smooth player progression will be a plus;
* Experience with level editors and tools used in game development;
* Knowledge of Unity and its level design capabilities or work with the levels editors;
* Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment;
* Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
* Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.

#### **WILL BE A PLUS:**


* Experience with casual games such as solitaire, match-3, or match-2 games;
* Familiarity with creating levels for mobile games;
* A portfolio showcasing previous work on similar projects will be a plus.

#### **RESPONSIBILITIES****:**


* Design and create captivating and balanced levels;
* Ensure levels are engaging, fun, and progressively challenging;
* Collaborate with the game design team to refine level mechanics and features;
* Adjust and balance levels based on player feedback and analytics;
* Work with difficulty curves to ensure a smooth and rewarding player experience;
* Utilize level editors and Unity to implement and test level designs;
* Continuously iterate and improve levels to maintain player interest and retention.

#### **OFFER:**


* Remote work;
* Open management without bureaucracy;
* Salary reviews according to the results of performance appraisal;
* 5 days paid sick leave and 18 working-days’ vacation;
* Days off on National/Bank Holidays according to the legislation of Ukraine;
* Conferences, knowledge sharing activities, certification;
* Availability of sabbatical;
* Possibility to grow inside the friendly and professional team.


**WHY YOU LIKE** **TO WORK WITH US**


**PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT**


* Training & development programs
* Open door policy
* Mentoring
**SALARY AND BONUSES**


* Paid leave
* Overtime pay
* Regular performance appraisal
**WORK SCHEDULE**


* Remote work
* Flexible hours
**OTHER PERKS**


* ENPS surveys
* Birth support
* Health program
